<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880527-0092 </DOCNO><HL> Harsco Division Wins $261 Million Contract For Trucks for Army </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HSC MD UTX ITT VRO GE BA HON </CO><IN> AUT ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Harsco Corp.'s BMY division won a $261 million Army contract for five-ton trucks.    Rolls-Royce Ltd. was awarded $96.7 million in Navy contracts for AV-8B Harrier jet engines.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. received $82.6 million in contracts for Navy AB-8B aircraft and for Army AH-64A helicopter gunships.    United Technologies Corp. got $69.3 million for Navy jet engine parts and for Army transport helicopters.    A joint venture between ITT Corp. and Varo Inc. won a $33.3 million Army contract for night-vision equipment.    Also, ITT's aerospace-optical division was given a $28 million addition to an Army contract for communications equipment.    General Electric Co. was awarded a $21.8 million Navy contract for shipboard combat systems.    Boeing Co. won a $13.7 million addition to an Air Force contract for KC-135 aircraft modifications.    Honeywell Inc. got an $11.2 million Army contract for artillery munitions. </TEXT></DOC>